The funeral of the late minister in the presidency Jackson Mthembu will be held in his hometown in Mpumalanga on Sunday. President Cyril Ramaphosa has accorded Mthembu an official (category 1) state funeral. He will be laid to rest in Emalahleni. Mthembu died of Covid-19 related complications on Thursday. There has beenÂ an outpouring of tributes in his honour.